      <p><a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">Achaierais</a> are massive, 15-foot-tall flightless birds that inhabit lawful planes of battle and are only occasionally encountered elsewhere.<a href="img/MonstersIntro-A.Achaierai.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/MonstersIntro-A.Achaierai.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <p><a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">Achaierais</a> speak <a href="ch75.html#EpicMonsters(A-E)57">Infernal</a>. They weigh about 750 pounds.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
        <div class="titlepage">
          <div>
            <div>
              <h5 class="title"><a name="id1616477"/>Combat</h5>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
          <div class="keyword">monsterinfo</div>
        </div>
        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A41"/>
        <p>In close combat, an <a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">achaierai</a> lashes out with two of its four legs and snaps with its powerful beak. It makes frequent use of its <a href="ch17s03.html#Feats349">Spring Attack</a> feat to strike quickly and then retreat out of range before an enemy can counterattack.</p>
        <p>An <a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">achaierai's</a> natural weapons, as well as any weapons it wields, are treated as evil-aligned and lawfulaligned for the purpose of overcoming damage reduction.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id1616536"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersIntro-A42"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Black Cloud (Ex):</strong></span> Up to three times per day an <a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">achaierai</a> can release a choking, toxic black cloud.</p>
          <p>Those other than <a href="ch60s03.html#MonstersIntro-A40">achaierai</a> within 10 feet instantly take 2d6 points of damage. They must also succeed on a DC 15 Fortitude save or be affected for 3 hours as though by an <span class="emphasis"><em><a href="ch47.html#SpellsH-L48">insanity</a></em></span> spell (caster level 16th). The save DC is Constitution-based.</p>
